@startuml
title Rendering Basics - Beginner Flow

skinparam ParticipantPadding 8

participant "Widget tree" as Widgets
participant "RenderSnapshotBuilder" as Builder
participant "RenderSnapshot" as Snapshot
participant "Render thread" as RenderThread
participant "RenderContext" as Context
participant "GPU" as GPU

Widgets -> Builder : append render units
Builder -> Snapshot : build immutable snapshot

... render tick ...

RenderThread -> Context : make current
RenderThread -> Snapshot : execute(context)
loop each render command
	Snapshot -> Context : execute command
	Context -> GPU : draw
end
RenderThread -> Context : present()

note right of Snapshot
A snapshot is a prepared list of drawing work.
It lets updating widgets and rendering frames
stay separated.
end note

@enduml
